external_knowledge:
- "beacons" here symbolically represent the types of announcements;
- "wandering eyes" is a metaphor for viewers or individuals interested in the announcements;
- "casting their light across the landscape of digital curiosity" suggests the visibility and engagement of the announcements;
- "bright lights" metaphorically refers to the announcement types that have garnered significant attention;
- "number of gazes" represents the total views received by each announcement type.

sql:
SELECT views, priority
FROM announcements
ORDER BY views DESC;

SELECT title, announcement_date, AVG(views) AS average_views
FROM announcements
GROUP BY title;

SELECT announcement_id, AVG(engagement_time) AS avg_engagement_time, COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) AS unique_users
FROM view_logs
GROUP BY announcement_id;

SELECT title, views
FROM announcements
WHERE priority = 'high';

SELECT views AS total_views
FROM announcements
WHERE announcement_id = 1;
